Workflow 3 - Image Pre Processing Stage

Aim

  • To Identify and Remove Images that will cause problems for the CNN Classification Task
  • These might be Blank Images, Occluded Images or Invalid Address Images
  • Uses Pytorch Library
  • Places365 Pretrained CNN Model Selector

Processing Stage 1 - Using Pre Trained Places365 CNN to Remove Outlier Images

  • PlacesCNN convolutional neural networks (CNNs) trained on Places365. Places365 is an Image DataSet of 1.8 million images from 365 scene categories(e.g. Phone Booth, Theatre or Field).
  • We use this Pytorch implemeted CNN to remove Google StreetView(SV) images that are occluded or that are not specificaly of a Building Type.
  • http://places2.csail.mit.edu

# PlacesCNN for scene classification
#
# by Bolei Zhou
# last modified by Bolei Zhou, Dec.27, 2017 with latest pytorch and torchvision 
#(upgrade your torchvision please if there is trn.Resize error)

# last modified by Anthony Sutton August 2017

def run_places(image):

    # load the pre-trained weights
    model_file = '%s_places365.pth.tar' % arch
    #print(model)
    if not os.access(model_file, os.W_OK):
        weight_url = 'http://places2.csail.mit.edu/models_places365/' + model_file
        os.system('wget ' + weight_url)

    model = models.__dict__[arch](num_classes=365)
    checkpoint = torch.load(model_file, map_location=lambda storage, loc: storage)
    state_dict = {str.replace(k,'module.',''): v for k,v in checkpoint['state_dict'].items()}
    model.load_state_dict(state_dict)
    model.eval()


    # load the image transformer
    centre_crop = trn.Compose([
            trn.Resize((256,256)),
            trn.CenterCrop(224),
            trn.ToTensor(),
            trn.Normalize([0.485, 0.456, 0.406], [0.229, 0.224, 0.225])
    ])

    # load the class label
    file_name = 'categories_places365.txt'
    if not os.access(file_name, os.W_OK):
        synset_url = 'https://raw.githubusercontent.com/csailvision/places365/master/categories_places365.txt'
        os.system('wget ' + synset_url)
    classes = list()
    with open(file_name) as class_file:
        for line in class_file:
            classes.append(line.strip().split(' ')[0][3:])
    classes = tuple(classes)

    # load the test image
    img_name = '12.jpg'
    if not os.access(img_name, os.W_OK):
        img_url = 'http://places.csail.mit.edu/demo/' + img_name
        os.system('wget ' + img_url)

    #img_name = '/Users/anthonysutton/ml2/_STREETVIEW_EXPLORER/LDD_Complete/Batch2/col_id_29335.jpg'
    img_name = image
    img = Image.open(img_name)
    input_img = V(centre_crop(img).unsqueeze(0))

    # forward pass
    logit = model.forward(input_img)
    #h_x = F.softmax(logit, 1).data.squeeze()
    h_x = F.softmax(logit).data.squeeze()
    probs, idx = h_x.sort(0, True)

    print('{} prediction on {}'.format(arch,img_name))
    # output the prediction
    #just extract class label - AS 03/08/2018
    for i in range(0, 1):
        
        #just extract class label - AS 03/08/2018
        category = classes[idx[i]]
        #print('{:.3f} -> {}'.format(probs[i], classes[idx[i]]))

    #return probs, idx, category
    return probs, category

                flag = False

#London Complete Clean
import os
import csv
#import pandas as pd
count = 0
with open('ldd_snow.csv') as csvfile:
    
    reader = csv.reader(csvfile)
    
    for row in reader:
        count = count + 1
        image = str(row[0])
        print(count)
        #print("deleting " + image)
        #> 29192
        image_str = os.path.basename(image)
        y = image_str.replace('col_id_','')
        z = y.replace('.jpg','')
        print(z)
        if int(z) <= 29192:
            image_del = '/Users/anthonysutton/ml2/_STREETVIEW_EXPLORER/LDD_Complete/' + os.path.basename(image)
            print("deleting " + image_del)
        elif int(z) > 29192:
            image_del = '/Users/anthonysutton/ml2/_STREETVIEW_EXPLORER/LDD_Complete/batch2/' + os.path.basename(image)
            print("deleting " + image_del)
        #print('del')
        os.remove(image_del)
print('done')

#/Users/anthonysutton/ml2/_LDD_EXPLORER/JULY13_RUN/ldd_totalafford_plus10.csv
#/Users/anthonysutton/ml2/_LDD_EXPLORER/JULY13_RUN/ldd_totalafford0_resiplus10_notjoined.csv!!!

    is_first_row = True
    for row in reader:
        # Skip the first row.
        if is_first_row:
            is_first_row = False
            continue
            
            
        #col, lat, lon = str(row[1]),  float(row[51]), float(row[52])

        #if (int(col)> 1 and int(col)< 48):
            #and "BR"in str(post)):          
            #& int(col)  < 138647
            location = (col, status, lat, lon)
            #print("location="+ str(location))
            locations.append(location)

            
print ("Done")
